Flight of the Pterosaurs

Science Documentary hosted by Ben Gazzara and published by Discovery Channel broadcasted as part of DC Paleoworld series in 1994 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Creationists have often pointed to the existence of flying animals, paleontologists begrudgingly had to admit that they had a point. What could possibly have been the progression? But now paleontologists are discovering and recreating the mechanisms by which the dinosaurs gradually adapted to flight; and they\&#039;re finding that the pterosaurs were once as diverse as modern birds.
